bishop of Ferns.  Mael-Maedóc Ó Morgair  (  1095–1148 ) was a reformer of the Church in Ireland and a friend of Bernard of Clairvaux. However, the modern Gaelic form (from  <i>c.</i>1200 ) is <i>Maol-Maodhóg</i> (pronounced ‘mul-<b>may</b>-og’), so that the name would have had to have been borrowed into English before this loss of the <i>d</i>. <i>Marmaduke</i> has never been common except in Yorkshire, where for example it was bourne by  Marmaduke Huby , abbot of Fountains, (  1495–1526 ). Its most notable bearer in recent times has been  Marmaduke Hussey  (  1923–2006 ), a former chairman of the governors of the BBC."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":20,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":29,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":64,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Marmaduke Darell was born about 1195, in Sessay, Yorkshire, England, his father, William Darrell, was 29 and his mother, Elizabeth de